o------------------------------------------------------------------------------o
|
| Siren
| A flexible 3D game engine
|
o------------------------------------------------------------------------------o


o------------------------------------------------------------------------------o
| Latest version
o------------------------------------------------------------------------------o

  Before going any further, you can check that this package you have is the
  latest version at the Siren download page.

        http://isugamedev.sf.net/siren/download.html


o------------------------------------------------------------------------------o
| Requirements
o------------------------------------------------------------------------------o

  There are several requirements necessary to compile and use Siren. Here is a
  list of the minimum requirements.

    * A good C++ compiler (g++ 3.x, MSVC7)
    * SCons 0.11
    * Audiere 1.9.1
    * Boost 1.30.0 + boost.python
    * Cal3D from CVS
    * Corona 1.0.1
    * GMTL from CVS
    * Python 2.2
    * SDL 1.2.5

  You can obtain SCons from the SCons Project Web site at:

        http://www.scons.org

  You can obtain Audiere from the Audiere Project Web site at:

        http://audiere.sourceforge.net

  You can obtain Boost from the Boost Project Web site at:

        http://boost.org

  You can obtain Cal3D from the Cal3D Project Web site at:

        http://cal3d.sourceforge.net

  You can obtain Corona from the Corona Project Web site at:

        http://corona.sourceforge.net

  You can obtain GMTL from the Generic Graphics Toolkit Project Web sit at:

        http://ggt.sourceforge.net

  You can obtain Python from the Python Project Web site at:

        http://python.org

  You can obtain SDL from the SDL Project Web site at:

        http://libsdl.org


o------------------------------------------------------------------------------o
| Documentation
o------------------------------------------------------------------------------o

  Installation instructions can be found in the INSTALL file.

  A quick and dirty tutorial can be found in the doc/tutorial.txt file.

  Siren API documentation is generated from source code using Doxygen which may
  be obtained from http://www.doxygen.org.

  Additional documentation for Siren is available at:

        http://isugamedev.sourceforge.net/siren

